@startuml seq-vm-migration
title VM Migration of a Sentinel (Live Migration)

participant "Orchestrator\n(k8s / ops)" as ops
participant "Old Sentinel\nInstance" as old_inst
participant "New Sentinel\nInstance" as new_inst
participant "Vault" as vault
participant "Discovery API" as disc
participant "Redis" as redis

note over ops
  VM migration scenario: 
  The Sentinel process must move to a new host/pod
  without changing its DID (key stays the same = same identity).
  The private key is in Vault, so the new instance just needs
  Vault AppRole credentials to bootstrap.
end note

== Step 1: Pre-migration — new instance starts ==

ops -> new_inst: Start new Sentinel pod\n(new IP, same service config)

new_inst -> vault: Authenticate (AppRole)\n{ role_id, secret_id }
vault --> new_inst: Vault token (lease TTL = 1h)

new_inst -> vault: Read private key\nsecret/sentinel/prod/consumer-app/private_key
vault --> new_inst: private_key_bytes
new_inst -> new_inst: Derive DID from key → same DID as old instance

new_inst -> disc: GET /api/v1/config\nAuthorization: Bearer <vault-token>\nX-Sentinel-DID: did:key:z6Mk<DID>
disc --> new_inst: signed config bundle
new_inst -> new_inst: Verify config bundle signature\nApply config

new_inst -> disc: GET /status/list-001 (warm up cache)
new_inst -> redis: Populate JTI cache connection

== Step 2: Traffic cutover ==

ops -> ops: Update load balancer / service mesh:\n  Remove old_inst from upstream pool\n  Add new_inst to upstream pool

note over old_inst, new_inst
  During cutover there may be in-flight requests.
  Both old and new instances accept requests.
  JTI replay cache is shared via Redis — 
  no duplicate JTI acceptance across instances.
end note

== Step 3: Old instance shutdown ==

ops -> old_inst: SIGTERM (graceful shutdown)
old_inst -> old_inst: Drain in-flight requests (grace period: 30s)
old_inst -> vault: Revoke Vault token (best-effort)
old_inst -> old_inst: Exit

== Post-migration verification ==

ops -> disc: GET /api/v1/sentinels/did:key:z6Mk<DID>
disc --> ops: 200 OK { status: ACTIVE, last_seen: <timestamp> }

note over new_inst
  The Sentinel DID is unchanged.
  All VCs issued to the old instance remain valid.
  No re-enrollment required.
  No key rotation required (key stayed in Vault).
end note

@enduml
